This is a guide to locating the encoded 3200 digits of $\pi$ in the [**Library of Babel**](https://libraryofbabel.info/).

## The Decoding Key

The decoding key is as follows:

| Character | Digit |
|:---------:|:-----:|
|     a     |   0   |
|     b     |   1   |
|     c     |   2   |
|     d     |   3   |
|     e     |   4   |
|     f     |   5   |
|     g     |   6   |
|     h     |   7   |
|     i     |   8   |
|     j     |   9   |
|     .     |   .   |
